text: Today, on a tour of Mack Point Terminal in Searsport, I was proud to announce that my Administration will evaluate how the Port can support the offshore wind industry. I look forward to the results of this assessment and charting a path forward for this industry in Maine. (2/2)

text: Today, a young cancer survivor & his family stood by my side as I signed An Act to Make March Maine Childhood Cancer Awareness Month. It is my hope that this designation will shine a light on its devastating impacts & demonstrate to Maine families that we stand with them. https://t.co/hoMUMtzImf

text: Today I was proud to welcome entrepreneurs to the Blaine House to share my new “Welcome Home” program - a data driven approach to marketing Maine and attracting talented people to our state. Thank you for your sharing your thoughts on creating a bright future for Maine! https://t.co/oumsrADyA7

text: Today I had the honor of meeting 91-year-old WWII veteran Conrad Lebourdais who joined the Navy when he was 17. Conrad presented me with one of his customized Louisville Slugger bats, which I will be honored to display in my office. Thank you for your service, Conrad. https://t.co/yzKyMKAemf

text: In my State of the State, I told the Legislature to send a bipartisan bill to expand affordable housing to my desk. Thanks to Rep. Ryan Fecteau, Sen. Pouliot & many others, I was proud to sign it into law today. I hope we can now say to thousands more Mainers, ‘welcome home’. https://t.co/9RsJTxeqWP
renderedContent: In my State of the State, I told the Legislature to send a bipartisan bill to expand affordable housing to my desk. Thanks to Rep. Ryan Fecteau, Sen. Pouliot & many others, I was proud to sign it into law today. I hope we can now say to thousands more Mainers, ‘welcome home’. https://t.co/9RsJTxeqWP

text: I have proposed increasing the state’s shamefully inadequate benefit for the families of our fallen first responders. We ask so much of the men and women who answer the call to service. Let us be there for their families in times of need. https://t.co/1GwDuf60gm
renderedContent: I have proposed increasing the state’s shamefully inadequate benefit for the families of our fallen first responders. We ask so much of the men and women who answer the call to service. Let us be there for their families in times of need. pressherald.com/2020/02/10/mai…

text: I have directed all State offices closed, and I urge Maine people to exercise extreme caution if they must be on the roads and to give our road crews and first responders plenty of room as they work to keep us safe. https://t.co/dnFuVWytea

text: These Justices, confirmed unanimously by the Maine Senate, have vast experience, sharp intellect, and measured temperament. I am confident they will render fair and impartial justice to the people of our great state. Congratulations on this notable achievement to you all. (2/2)

text: Today I presented a supplemental budget proposal which sets aside $20 million in our Rainy Day Fund; strengthens services that protect the health, safety and well-being of Maine families; and enhances workforce and economic development. https://t.co/zWyA7zUYfc https://t.co/34pnqtYWIs

text: Today I signed into law two pieces of legislation to help combat poverty in Maine. Maine is confronting a workforce shortage that will be solved, in part, by making sure that every able adult is working and every child is getting a good education that will allow them to flourish. https://t.co/Rp3nZeVU1C

text: Today, I signed into law three major pieces of bipartisan legislation (LD 1679, LD 1494 and LD 1711) that will help usher in renewable energy in Maine, create clean energy jobs, and fight climate change. Maine is once again leading on clean energy. #mepolitics https://t.co/umDksdB0ff

text: The outrageous prices of prescription drugs are hurting Mainers, especially older Mainers on a fixed income. text: I was honored to thank a group of brave Scouts for their heroic actions in rescuing two men who had fallen out of their canoe into the frigid waters of Umsaskis Lake in northern Maine earlier this month. text: When I took office, I gave my word to Mainers suffering from substance use disorder.  I told them that, together, we will do everything in our power to bring them back, to make our communities, our families, and our state whole once again.  https://t.co/RDyM0XUa5A

text: The first meeting of Maine's reinstated Children's Cabinet! (Just don't tell my Commissioners). text: Honored to meet a group of veterans visiting the State House today! There is no reason someone who has served their country in the military should not have access to housing, food, & the services they need. I will continue to work to honor our veterans & their service. https://t.co/9Ho3bNh4Mi

text: As Governor, I am committed to working to reduce the rate of heart disease & stroke in Maine by working to keep our kids from becoming addicted to nicotine and helping others quit. text: Today I was proud to announce that Gordon Smith, an experienced, well-respected, and highly qualified public health expert, will serve as my Director of Opioid Response.
